# Enumerated independently of TRUSTED_DELIVERY_STATUS_RUNTIME_DIGESTS above, so that
# `materialize_delivery_status_runtime`'s set comparison is an actual cross-check: adding a script
# to one inventory and forgetting the other must fail closed rather than silently agree. Deriving
# this from the digest map's own keys would make that check unfailable.
#
# There were three enumerations here until v16-r28. The third, DELIVERY_STATUS_RUNTIME_INVENTORY,
# carried this same rationale but was referenced by nothing — the cross-check it claimed to make
# real compares the two maps that are actually used, and never read the tuple. A list that no code
# reads cannot fail closed; it only offers a fourth thing to drift and a comment that reads as a
# guarantee. Two independently hand-written enumerations plus the set comparison is the check.
